runs.comm: goes past the outside edge as he pushes at a wide delivery.
defends with an angled bat to the off side.
back of length and beats the outside edge.
cut in the air and behind the wicket on the off side for a boundary.
driven wonderfully well through the off side to the fence.
outside edge drops just short of the keeper to the fence.
hit in the air over extra cover.
defended straight back to the bowler.
punches to mid-on.
cut away hard behind point.
appeal for a lbw turned down and during the process, the throw misses the stumps and goes to the fence.
played with an angled bat behind point.
one bounce into the fence, hit in the air over extra cover.
outside edge along the ground behind point.
defended back to the bowler.
defended.
driven along the ground to extra cover.
outside edge along the ground to short thirdman.
down the track and mistimes to mid-on.
bouncer goes way over the head of the batsman.
another bouncer and Kinchit hooks well to the fine leg fence.
top-edge as he pulls, gets it over the keeper to the fence, a desperate dive near the boundary.
cuts it behind point.
pulls and misses.
driven along the ground to mid-off.
punches to the off side to mid-off.
backs away and cuts behind point.
off the pad behind the wicket on the off side.
dropped by the keeper.
edges it behind the wicket on the onside.
sweeps it well over the square leg fence for a six.
works it gently through the onside for couple of runs.
another couple of runs through the onside.
off the pad to the off side.
one bounce to the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
outside edge down to thirdman fence.
goes for a big slog and misses it.
works it to the onside.
sweeps and misses.
going on with the arm and strikes the pad in line, loud appeal and given.
plays and misses outside the off stump.
pushes to the off side.
driven to the off side to extra cover.
works it through the vacant midwicket.
lovely shot and in the slot and driven well along the ground through extra cover.
dabs it behind point and takes off for a non-existent single, shy at the stumps misses, Babar Hayat had given up.
cut in the air down to thirdman.
hit in the air down to long off and the fielder in the process of going for the catch, drops just short of him and goes to the fence.
driven to the off side for a single.
mistimes the pull.
off the pad to the onside.
looking to work it through the onside, misses it.
pushes to the onside for a quick single.
goes all the way, picks it up and launches it over the square leg fence for a six.
inside edges to the onside.
hit in the air down to long off and one bounce to the fielder.
played back to the bowler.
works to the onside but straight to the fielder.
hits hard down the ground to long on.
played to mid-on.
hit hard in the air to deep midwicket and Shenwari takes a good catch.
tucks it behind square leg for a single.
dabs it down to thirdman.
inside edge and off the pads and down to the fine leg fence.
gets it behind square leg for a single.
tucks it to square leg.
blocked to the off side.

tossed up delivery outside off. Chapman pre-meditates his shot as he skips down the track and tries to loft that over the off side. He doesn't gets to the pitch of the ball as he skies to the right of the fielder down at long-off.  Naib ran across to hold that.
flatter length ball on the middle and leg, clips it down to long-on
touch quicker and on a length, edges it to the left of short third man..
comes down the track and drags it flat and uppishly over the bowler's head and gets a boundary
that turns in with the angle from round the wicket, touch flat and on a length. Batsman misses out the clip and took it on the pad, heading down leg.
on middle and leg, waits on the crease and nudges this to wide of midwicket, gets back for the second..
comes round the wicket and gets in it on a length just outside off, batsman pokes at it and his beaten by the extra bounce and there is touch of inward movement with the angle..
once again this one jags back in with good bounce beating the outside edge. Nizakat was caught at the crease as he tries to dab that towards third man..

and finally he gets the wicket, nothing changes from Zadran though Nizakat looks unhappy as he walks back. This was touch shortish just around the off stump and zips across making the batsman play. He was caught in that cordon where must play that line and possibly gets an outside edge to the keeper but Nizakat doesn't feel the same way. He was backing away there touch and tries to run that to third man with an open face..
short of a length and angling into the batsman, left alone..
waits on the crease and steers this back of a length ball down to third man for a single..
short of a length on the hips, works it infront of square leg for a quick single
full ball around the off stump, nudges it through wide of midwicket
flatter and shortish ball just outside off, strides forward and blocks it infront of cover for another quick single..
comes out and clips this flat length ball to the left of the bowler..
slogs this short ball across the line to wide of running deepish square leg, not from the meat of it and probably that saved him too..

this time he holes out..Nabi gets his fourth..He drags this short as Afzal skips down the track in search of a mighty hoick over the leg side. He was nowhere near to the line and just ends up slicing it down towards the long-on where Naib hardly moved from his place to pouch that dolly..
pushes quick and flat outside off, beaten
backs away to this short ball as he carves it away to wide of extra cover..

Rath keeps the dancing shoes on and was looking out to hit this flat length ball over the bowler's head. This was the leggie, which was pitched outside the leg stump and goes past the swinging bat of Rath. Keeper does the rest..
that's the wrong'un, spun back sharply and brushes the pad, heading down leg..
another googly, once again he is beaten but gets a leg bye down the leg side..
pushes this length ball across of the bowler..
short and kept touch low and turning in, goes through the swinging bat of Khan..
short of a length ball on middle and leg, jabs it down the track for a single..
back of a length ball outside off, punches uppishly over the extra cover region
kept the shortish length on middle stump, waits and pushes it from the crease towards backward point.
alters the length outside off as he pushes this touch uppish, Aizaz stays on the crease and slices that over the extra cover region. Stanikzai ran across to his left and holds a good running catch..
length ball as he drags this down off the inside half to long-on
full ball on the off stump, squeezes it out through cover point..
length ball angling down the leg side, clips the pad and rolls to behind the keeper..
that's a googly, turning back in from a length, took it on the pad but impact was outside off..

another wrong'un from Rashid. This one kept touch low and turns back in sharply from outside off. He stays on the crease and tries to cut that, not enough room for that and that ball clips the back pad. Straight-forward decision..
once again kept the googly, as this one clips the pad down the leg side..

and Dawlat keeps the Afghanistan hopes alive. This was bowled from wide of the crease and back of a length coming in with the angle. Hits the pad of Tanveer quite low as he plays all across the line and umpire raises his finger.
